               <floruit notBefore="1865" notAfter="1922">He was one of the few
                  learned officials of <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Mǝnilǝk</persName>.
                  He was small in size and physically frail, but he exercised an immense influence both in political and ecclesiastical affairs. 
                  He started his career as a clerk in the court of <persName ref="PRS2342Bafana"/> from where he was transferred to the service of 
                  <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> in <date>1870</date>'s. In <date>1893</date>, he raised to the position
                  of liqa kāhǝnāt of the state and head of <placeName ref="LOC2364DabraS"/> church of <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/>. He continued to serve during the reign of 
                  <persName ref="PRS5620IyasuV"/> and the first seven years of the reign of <persName ref="PRS10671Zawditu"/>. </floruit>
               <death when="1922"> He died of illness and was buried at the <placeName ref="LOC6064Urael"/> 
                  <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/>.</death>
                     
                     
